  "diffSummary": "Reconciliation of the QR-login feature merged in f343624 (its code shipped but the harness tracking was never completed; the contract required a live phone scan that could not be run by the agent). The zalo layer's run_qr_login wraps zca-rust API::login_qr, maps each LoginQREvent to a non-secret QrLoginEvent display DTO (dropping the token-bearing GotLoginInfo), generates a stable per-account imei (ADR-0004), and assembles a reusable types::Credentials from the QR cookie jar + user agent. command/start_qr_login streams QR display events to the UI over the zalo://qr Tauri event and, on success, establishes the session entirely in-core (credential triple never crosses IPC). The frontend QrLoginScreen.svelte renders the QR image, countdown, scanned avatar/name preview, and declined/success states. This reconciliation captures the previously-missing live proof: the project owner completed a real phone QR scan against the running app and the captured non-secret core log shows the full flow (start_qr_login -> 6 cookies incl. zpw_sek extracted from the jar -> QR confirmed -> credential persisted -> session established -> ui success).",
  "changedFiles": [
    "src-tauri/src/types/qr.rs",
    "src-tauri/src/types/mod.rs",
    "src-tauri/src/zalo/mod.rs",
    "src-tauri/src/command/mod.rs"
  ],
